FBIS4-13521 "drnes077dd_94004" FBIS-NES-94-077 Daily Report 21 Apr 1994 Palestinian Affairs Political Department Slated To Move to Cairo Political Department Slated To Move to Cairo JN2104110594 Amman AKHBAR AL-USBU' in Arabic 21 Apr 94 p 1 JN2104110594 Amman AKHBAR AL-USBU' Arabic BFN [Text] Cairo--It has become certain that the PLO Political Department will be moved from Tunis to Cairo within the next weeks. AKHBAR AL-USBU' learned that final preparations have been completed to move the Political Department. Informed sources expect that this will be the beginning of moving all PLO departments from Tunis to Cairo in the coming months. Meanwhile, the Tunisian Government has decided not to renew the residency of any Palestinian in Tunisia as of late last month. The government gave instructions to the concerned authorities to deport any Palestinian as soon as his residency expires. Scores of Palestinians, whose residency permits expired, have been deported, and all Palestinians are expected to be deported from Tunisia by the end of this year.
